@startuml Auth-Sequence-Diagram
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam maxMessageSize 200

title Sistema de Autenticación JWT con MFA\nDiagramas de Secuencia

' ===============================================
' ACTORS Y PARTICIPANTS
' ===============================================

actor "Usuario" as User
participant "Angular\nFrontend" as Frontend
participant "Auth\nInterceptor" as Interceptor
participant "Django\nAPI" as API
participant "Auth\nMiddleware" as Middleware
participant "Auth\nService" as AuthService
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
database "Redis\nCache" as Redis
participant "Email\nService" as Email

' ===============================================
' SECUENCIA 1: LOGIN BÁSICO CON JWT
' ===============================================

== 1. Login Básico con JWT ==

User -> Frontend: Ingresa email y password
activate Frontend

Frontend -> API: POST /api/v1/auth/login\n{email, password}
activate API

API -> Middleware: Verificar rate limit
activate Middleware
Middleware -> Redis: Incrementar contador\npara IP
Redis --> Middleware: OK (3/100 intentos)
Middleware --> API: ✓ Permitir
deactivate Middleware

API -> AuthService: authenticate(email, password)
activate AuthService

AuthService -> DB: SELECT * FROM user\nWHERE email = ?
activate DB
DB --> AuthService: User record
deactivate DB

AuthService -> AuthService: verify_password()\n[bcrypt.verify()]

alt Password correcto
    AuthService -> DB: UPDATE user\nSET last_login = NOW()
    activate DB
    DB --> AuthService: OK
    deactivate DB

    AuthService -> AuthService: generate_access_token()\n[exp: 15 min, claims: user_id,\ntenant_id, roles, permissions]

    AuthService -> AuthService: generate_refresh_token()\n[exp: 7 days]

    AuthService -> DB: INSERT INTO refresh_token\n(user_id, token_hash, expires_at)
    activate DB
    DB --> AuthService: Token created
    deactivate DB

    AuthService -> DB: INSERT INTO audit_log\n(action='login', user_id, ip)
    activate DB
    DB --> AuthService: Log created
    deactivate DB

    AuthService --> API: {access_token, refresh_token,\nuser, tenant, permissions}
    deactivate AuthService

    API --> Frontend: 200 OK\n{access_token, refresh_token, user}
    deactivate API

    Frontend -> Frontend: localStorage.setItem(\n'access_token', token)
    Frontend -> Frontend: localStorage.setItem(\n'refresh_token', token)

    Frontend --> User: ✓ Redirigir a Dashboard
    deactivate Frontend

else Password incorrecto
    AuthService -> DB: INSERT INTO audit_log\n(action='login_failed')
    activate DB
    DB --> AuthService: OK
    deactivate DB

    AuthService -> Redis: Incrementar\nfailed_attempts(email)
    Redis --> AuthService: Count = 3

    alt Intentos >= 5
        AuthService -> Redis: SET lockout:{email}\nEXPIRE 900 (15 min)
        AuthService --> API: Account locked
        API --> Frontend: 429 Too Many Requests\n{error: "Account locked"}
        Frontend --> User: ✗ Cuenta bloqueada\n15 minutos
    else Intentos < 5
        AuthService --> API: Invalid credentials
        API --> Frontend: 401 Unauthorized\n{error: "Invalid credentials"}
        Frontend --> User: ✗ Email o password\ninválido
    end

end

' ===============================================
' SECUENCIA 2: REQUEST CON ACCESS TOKEN
' ===============================================

newpage Request con Access Token

== 2. Request Protegido con Access Token ==

User -> Frontend: Navega a /users
activate Frontend

Frontend -> Interceptor: GET /api/v1/users
activate Interceptor

Interceptor -> Interceptor: token = localStorage\n.getItem('access_token')

Interceptor -> API: GET /api/v1/users\nAuthorization: Bearer {token}
deactivate Interceptor
activate API

API -> Middleware: Validar JWT
activate Middleware

Middleware -> Middleware: jwt.decode(token)

alt Token válido y no expirado
    Middleware -> Redis: GET cached_permissions:\n{user_id}:{tenant_id}
    activate Redis

    alt Cache hit
        Redis --> Middleware: [permissions list]
    else Cache miss
        Middleware -> DB: SELECT permissions\nFROM roles JOIN tenant_membership
        activate DB
        DB --> Middleware: [permissions list]
        deactivate DB

        Middleware -> Redis: SET cached_permissions\nTTL 300 (5 min)
        Redis --> Middleware: OK
    end
    deactivate Redis

    Middleware -> Middleware: request.user = user\nrequest.tenant = tenant\nrequest.permissions = perms

    Middleware --> API: ✓ Usuario autenticado
    deactivate Middleware

    API -> API: @require_permission('users.read')

    alt Usuario tiene permiso
        API -> DB: SELECT * FROM user\nWHERE tenant_id = ?\n[RLS enforcement]
        activate DB
        DB --> API: Users list
        deactivate DB

        API --> Frontend: 200 OK\n{users: [...]}
        Frontend --> User: ✓ Mostrar lista usuarios

    else Usuario NO tiene permiso
        API --> Frontend: 403 Forbidden\n{error: "Permission denied"}
        Frontend --> User: ✗ No autorizado
    end

else Token expirado
    Middleware --> API: Token expired
    deactivate Middleware
    API --> Frontend: 401 Unauthorized\n{error: "token_expired"}
    deactivate API

    note right of Frontend
        Frontend detecta token_expired
        y ejecuta flujo de refresh
    end note

    Frontend -> Frontend: trigger_token_refresh()
    ref over Frontend, API, DB
        Ver: "3. Refresh Token"
    end ref

else Token inválido (firma incorrecta)
    Middleware --> API: Invalid token
    API --> Frontend: 401 Unauthorized\n{error: "invalid_token"}
    Frontend -> Frontend: logout()
    Frontend --> User: ✗ Redirigir a Login
end

deactivate Frontend

' ===============================================
' SECUENCIA 3: REFRESH TOKEN
' ===============================================

newpage Refresh Token

== 3. Refresh de Access Token ==

Frontend -> API: POST /api/v1/auth/refresh\n{refresh_token}
activate Frontend
activate API

API -> AuthService: validate_refresh_token(token)
activate AuthService

AuthService -> AuthService: token_hash = SHA256(token)

AuthService -> DB: SELECT * FROM refresh_token\nWHERE token_hash = ?\nAND expires_at > NOW()\nAND revoked_at IS NULL
activate DB
DB --> AuthService: RefreshToken record
deactivate DB

alt Refresh token válido
    AuthService -> AuthService: generate_new_access_token()\n[exp: 15 min]

    note right of AuthService
        **Token Rotation (Security Best Practice)**
        Generar nuevo refresh token y
        revocar el anterior
    end note

    AuthService -> AuthService: new_refresh = generate_refresh_token()

    AuthService -> DB: UPDATE refresh_token\nSET revoked_at = NOW()\nWHERE id = old_token_id
    activate DB
    DB --> AuthService: OK
    deactivate DB

    AuthService -> DB: INSERT INTO refresh_token\n(user_id, token_hash, expires_at)
    activate DB
    DB --> AuthService: New token created
    deactivate DB

    AuthService --> API: {new_access_token,\nnew_refresh_token}
    deactivate AuthService

    API --> Frontend: 200 OK\n{access_token, refresh_token}
    deactivate API

    Frontend -> Frontend: localStorage.setItem(\n'access_token', new_token)
    Frontend -> Frontend: localStorage.setItem(\n'refresh_token', new_token)

    Frontend -> Frontend: retry_original_request()

    Frontend --> User: ✓ Request exitoso\n(transparente)
    deactivate Frontend

else Refresh token inválido/expirado
    AuthService --> API: Invalid refresh token
    API --> Frontend: 401 Unauthorized\n{error: "invalid_refresh"}
    Frontend -> Frontend: logout()
    Frontend -> Frontend: localStorage.clear()
    Frontend --> User: ✗ Redirigir a Login
end

' ===============================================
' SECUENCIA 4: LOGIN CON MFA (TOTP)
' ===============================================

newpage Login con MFA

== 4. Login con MFA (Multi-Factor Authentication) ==

User -> Frontend: Ingresa email y password
activate Frontend

Frontend -> API: POST /api/v1/auth/login\n{email, password}
activate API

API -> AuthService: authenticate(email, password)
activate AuthService

AuthService -> DB: SELECT * FROM user\nWHERE email = ?
activate DB
DB --> AuthService: User record\n(mfa_enabled = true)
deactivate DB

AuthService -> AuthService: verify_password()\n[bcrypt.verify()]

alt Password correcto Y MFA enabled
    note right of AuthService
        No emitir tokens todavía,
        esperar código TOTP
    end note

    AuthService -> AuthService: session_token = generate_temp_session()

    AuthService -> Redis: SET mfa_pending:{session_token}\nVALUE: {user_id}\nEXPIRE 300 (5 min)
    activate Redis
    Redis --> AuthService: OK
    deactivate Redis

    AuthService --> API: MFA required
    deactivate AuthService

    API --> Frontend: 200 OK\n{mfa_required: true,\nsession_token}
    deactivate API

    Frontend --> User: Solicitar código TOTP
    deactivate Frontend

    User -> Frontend: Ingresa código 6 dígitos\n(from Google Authenticator)
    activate Frontend

    Frontend -> API: POST /api/v1/auth/mfa/verify\n{session_token, totp_code}
    activate API

    API -> AuthService: verify_totp(session_token, code)
    activate AuthService

    AuthService -> Redis: GET mfa_pending:{session_token}
    activate Redis
    Redis --> AuthService: {user_id}
    deactivate Redis

    AuthService -> DB: SELECT mfa_secret FROM user\nWHERE id = ?
    activate DB
    DB --> AuthService: mfa_secret (encrypted)
    deactivate DB

    AuthService -> AuthService: decrypt(mfa_secret)

    AuthService -> AuthService: verify_totp_code()\n[pyotp.TOTP(secret).verify(code)]

    alt Código TOTP correcto
        AuthService -> Redis: DEL mfa_pending:{session_token}

        AuthService -> AuthService: generate_access_token()
        AuthService -> AuthService: generate_refresh_token()

        AuthService -> DB: INSERT INTO refresh_token
        activate DB
        DB --> AuthService: OK
        deactivate DB

        AuthService -> DB: INSERT INTO audit_log\n(action='login_mfa', user_id)
        activate DB
        DB --> AuthService: OK
        deactivate DB

        AuthService --> API: {access_token,\nrefresh_token, user}
        deactivate AuthService

        API --> Frontend: 200 OK\n{access_token, refresh_token}
        deactivate API

        Frontend -> Frontend: localStorage.setItem(tokens)
        Frontend --> User: ✓ Redirigir a Dashboard
        deactivate Frontend

    else Código TOTP incorrecto
        AuthService -> Redis: INCR mfa_attempts:{session_token}
        Redis --> AuthService: attempts = 2

        alt Intentos >= 3
            AuthService -> Redis: DEL mfa_pending:{session_token}
            AuthService --> API: Max attempts exceeded
            API --> Frontend: 429 Too Many Requests
            Frontend --> User: ✗ Demasiados intentos,\nvolver a login
        else Intentos < 3
            AuthService --> API: Invalid TOTP code
            API --> Frontend: 401 Unauthorized\n{remaining_attempts: 1}
            Frontend --> User: ✗ Código incorrecto,\nintentar nuevamente
        end
    end

else Password incorrecto
    AuthService --> API: Invalid credentials
    API --> Frontend: 401 Unauthorized
    Frontend --> User: ✗ Credenciales inválidas
end

' ===============================================
' SECUENCIA 5: LOGOUT
' ===============================================

newpage Logout

== 5. Logout ==

User -> Frontend: Click "Logout"
activate Frontend

Frontend -> API: POST /api/v1/auth/logout\n{refresh_token}\nAuthorization: Bearer {access_token}
activate API

API -> AuthService: logout(user, refresh_token)
activate AuthService

AuthService -> DB: UPDATE refresh_token\nSET revoked_at = NOW()\nWHERE token_hash = ?
activate DB
DB --> AuthService: Token revoked
deactivate DB

AuthService -> DB: UPDATE session\nSET is_active = false\nWHERE user_id = ?\nAND is_active = true
activate DB
DB --> AuthService: Session terminated
deactivate DB

AuthService -> Redis: DEL cached_permissions:\n{user_id}:{tenant_id}
activate Redis
Redis --> AuthService: OK
deactivate Redis

AuthService -> DB: INSERT INTO audit_log\n(action='logout', user_id)
activate DB
DB --> AuthService: OK
deactivate DB

AuthService --> API: Logout successful
deactivate AuthService

API --> Frontend: 200 OK
deactivate API

Frontend -> Frontend: localStorage.clear()
Frontend -> Frontend: sessionStorage.clear()
Frontend -> Frontend: authService.clearState()

Frontend --> User: ✓ Redirigir a Login
deactivate Frontend

' ===============================================
' NOTAS Y LEYENDAS
' ===============================================

note over User, Email
  **Security Features Implementadas:**
  • Password hashing con bcrypt (cost 12)
  • JWT con claims mínimos (no permisos completos)
  • Refresh token rotation (previene replay attacks)
  • Rate limiting (100 req/min por IP)
  • Account lockout tras 5 intentos fallidos (15 min)
  • MFA con TOTP (Google Authenticator compatible)
  • Cache de permisos con TTL 5 min
  • Audit log inmutable de todos los eventos auth
  • Session tracking con revocación remota
  • Row-Level Security en PostgreSQL
end note

legend right
  |= Status Code |= Significado |
  | 200 OK | Request exitoso |
  | 401 Unauthorized | Token inválido/expirado |
  | 403 Forbidden | Sin permisos |
  | 429 Too Many Requests | Rate limit excedido |

  **Token Lifetimes:**
  • Access Token: 15 minutos
  • Refresh Token: 7 días
  • MFA Session: 5 minutos
  • Account Lockout: 15 minutos

  **Cache Strategy:**
  • Permissions: 5 minutos (Redis)
  • Failed attempts: 1 hora (Redis)
  • MFA pending: 5 minutos (Redis)
endlegend

@enduml
